      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "The 'Test samples' factor addresses variability arising from physical specimen-to-specimen manufacturing differences in validation hardware. For this COU, the validation activity uses a single FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry defined by a fixed CAD file from the FDA benchmark repository; there is no population of manufactured physical test articles with dimensional variability. The computational geometry is deterministic and does not exhibit sample-to-sample variation. Therefore, this factor does not apply to the present simulation credibility assessment at MRL 2 for a geometry-fixed benchmark model."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "The 'Equivalency of input parameters' factor is applicable when the validation experiment employs surrogate or scaled boundary conditions that differ from the COU conditions, requiring a formal equivalency argument. In this assessment, the validation experiments were conducted directly at CPB-representative operating conditions (2–6 L/min, 3000–5000 RPM, 37°C, hematocrit 33%) using the same pump geometry as the COU. No scaling laws, surrogate fluids with adjusted properties, or non-representative boundary conditions were employed. Because the validation and COU input parameters are directly matched without substitution, a separate equivalency argument is not required and this factor does not apply."
    }
